Name: common bile duct neoplasm
Definition: A hepatobiliary system cancer that results_in malignant growth located_in the gallbladder or located_in the bile duct.

Name: biliary tract intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm
Definition: A biliary tract benign neoplasm characterized by multiple papillary tumors in the intrahepatic and/or extrahepatic biliary tree.

Name: obsolete tumor of the thecoma fibroma group
Definition: A biliary tract benign neoplasm characterized by multiple papillary tumors in the intrahepatic and/or extrahepatic biliary tree.
